networks.ThreeWindingTransformer.ThreeWindingTransformer¶

class networks.ThreeWindingTransformer.ThreeWindingTransformer(name, hv_bus_id, mv_bus_id, lv_bus_id, hv_kv, mv_kv, lv_kv, sn_hv_kva, sn_mv_kva, sn_lv_kva, vk_hv_percent, vk_mv_percent, vk_lv_percent, vkr_hv_percent, vkr_mv_percent, vkr_lv_percent, pfe_kw, i0_percent, tap_min, tap_neutral, tap_max, tap_step_percent, rh, rm, rl, xh, xm, xl)¶

Bases: Element

Represents a three-winding transformer element in a power system network.

Parameters:

  • name (str) – The name of the three-winding transformer.

  • hv_bus_id (int) – The ID of the high-voltage (HV) bus where the transformer is connected.

  • mv_bus_id (int) – The ID of the medium-voltage (MV) bus where the transformer is connected.

  • lv_bus_id (int) – The ID of the low-voltage (LV) bus where the transformer is connected.

  • hv_kv (float) – The high-voltage (HV) rating of the transformer in kilovolts (kV).

  • mv_kv (float) – The medium-voltage (MV) rating of the transformer in kilovolts (kV).

  • lv_kv (float) – The low-voltage (LV) rating of the transformer in kilovolts (kV).

  • sn_hv_kva (float) – The apparent power rating of the transformer at high voltage (HV) side in kilovolt-amperes (kVA).

  • sn_mv_kva (float) – The apparent power rating of the transformer at medium voltage (MV) side in kilovolt-amperes (kVA).

  • sn_lv_kva (float) – The apparent power rating of the transformer at low voltage (LV) side in kilovolt-amperes (kVA).

  • vk_hv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage percentage of the transformer at high voltage (HV) side.

  • vk_mv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage percentage of the transformer at medium voltage (MV) side.

  • vk_lv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage percentage of the transformer at low voltage (LV) side.

  • vkr_hv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage resistance percentage of the transformer at high voltage (HV) side.

  • kr_mv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage resistance percentage of the transformer at medium voltage (MV) side.

  • vkr_lv_percent (float) – The short-circuit voltage resistance percentage of the transformer at low voltage (LV) side.

  • pfe_kw (float) – Iron losses in the transformer in kilowatts (kW).

  • i0_percent (float) – No-load current percentage of the transformer.

  • tap_min (float) – Minimum tap position of the transformer.

  • tap_neutral (float) – Neutral tap position of the transformer.

  • tap_max (float) – Maximum tap position of the transformer.

  • tap_step_percent (float) – Tap step percentage of the transformer.

  • rh (float) – Resistance at high voltage (HV) side of the transformer.

  • rm (float) – Resistance at medium voltage (MV) side of the transformer.

  • rl (float) – Resistance at low voltage (LV) side of the transformer.

  • xh (float) – Reactance at high voltage (HV) side of the transformer.

  • xm (float) – Reactance at medium voltage (MV) side of the transformer.

  • xl (float) – Reactance at low voltage (LV) side of the transformer.
